{"title":"Infecciones del SNC","guid":"","filepath":"/Users/criaah/Vault/📚 Resources/Mapas-Mentales/Entidades clínicas/Infectología/Infecciones del SNC-2024-1.smmx","root":{"id":"0","parent":"-1","text":"Urgencias\\NNeuroinfecciosas","guid":"oVyKl33FSsxV2Wsn0XmaYQ","children":[{"id":"1","parent":"0","text":"Emergencias\\Nneuroinfecciosas","guid":"ymNHeAa9Yu0qqGbu_-f3dQ","children":[{"id":"2","parent":"1","text":"1. Definición y\\Ngeneralidades","guid":"","children":[{"id":"3","parent":"2","text":"• Infección S.N → Emergencia médica.","guid":"sTIE_fL2MJmlISgIBMdHcw","children":[]},{"id":"4","parent":"2","text":"• Meningitis y encefalitis: confusión con otros dx (p. ej. ACV o tumor).","guid":"4kxnLN2O31VOhqT2nMb_dA","children":[]},{"id":"5","parent":"2","text":"• Sospecha alta → Dx y tratamiento temprano ↓ morbilidad y mortalidad.","guid":"TCsI8ET3VxwMyJiEl-dO3w","children":[]}]},{"id":"6","parent":"1","text":"2. Tipos de infecciones\\Ndel S. N","guid":"X1uBmO6ZU0TbTc1DZBNUTQ","children":[{"id":"7","parent":"6","text":"• Encefalitis y Mielitis","guid":"a4PgmBpiNaibwSjjLrNCRw","children":[]},{"id":"8","parent":"6","text":"• Inflamación cerebral (encefalitis) y medular (mielitis).","guid":"nEKaUTEYkPoUY_cAqQpFZg","children":[]},{"id":"9","parent":"6","text":"• Etiología viral en el 30-50% de los casos con causa identificada.","guid":"E_T72ENVIgwuloV-6StVxw","children":[]},{"id":"10","parent":"6","text":"• Virus más comunes: VHS-1 (herpes), enterovirus, arbovirus, otros herpesvirus.","guid":"yvm-EKLCBI4rTg_KaGbB2A","children":[]},{"id":"11","parent":"6","text":"• Mortalidad 6% en hospitalizados, ↑ en VIH (10%) o trasplante (17%).","guid":"9c0w8ZIlfQ8zXSC8SGj-mw","children":[]}]},{"id":"12","parent":"1","text":"3. Etiologías\\Nvirales","guid":"hGs6eEe8AWMapgsZAfDkoQ","children":[{"id":"13","parent":"12","text":"• Herpesvirus","guid":"y2ZknWvHoG6LZFMI0SEQfg","children":[{"id":"14","parent":"13","text":"• VHS, VVZ, CMV → tto con aciclovir, valaciclovir, ganciclovir, foscarnet.","guid":"_H0b_OPINGhciWqI97Aq0Q","children":[]},{"id":"15","parent":"13","text":"• EBV, HHV-6 → tto de soporte.","guid":"LwkBSP2j4MeqAur3TpbK_A","children":[]}]},{"id":"16","parent":"12","text":"• Enterovirus (EV 71, coxsackie, polio) → soporte.","guid":"CD527NZ3wxlxH4x6Zrw0TA","children":[]},{"id":"17","parent":"12","text":"• Arbovirus (West Nile, encefalitis japonesa, Powassan, SLE, encefalitis equina, dengue, zika)\\N→ soporte, posible IgIV.","guid":"qxjYHlayHUIVuzqEFlPRkQ","children":[]},{"id":"18","parent":"12","text":"• Rhabdovirus (Rabia) → IgR humana + vacuna.","guid":"xUhMbN1K0qm8WJdMA_y5NQ","children":[]},{"id":"19","parent":"12","text":"• Alphainfluenzavirus (influenza A) → soporte.","guid":"dJCyYRnPV4gCFxiu8xE5vQ","children":[]}]},{"id":"20","parent":"1","text":"4. Complicaciones\\Nemergentes","guid":"Gss0pQ0IVVzRoJ74iXZx2Q","children":[{"id":"21","parent":"20","text":"• Edema cerebral, herniación.","guid":"nZzs6aeI3cHxgonCdOTRLw","children":[]},{"id":"22","parent":"20","text":"• Compresión medular.","guid":"SKfWRUFEb4Zs_v7Iy23DBg","children":[]},{"id":"23","parent":"20","text":"• Hidrocefalia.","guid":"yjS9Yiq1ftVILtt4u7sQXw","children":[]},{"id":"24","parent":"20","text":"• Vasculopatía → ACV isquémico.","guid":"hJP-75GbefdddpGhXcEs9Q","children":[]},{"id":"25","parent":"20","text":"• Trombosis venosa.","guid":"pBjfXmQuLpGq2xUIyqv9-g","children":[]},{"id":"26","parent":"20","text":"• Hemorragia intracerebral.","guid":"3HOhcl14CYciLTuOhBU2qg","children":[]},{"id":"27","parent":"20","text":"• Status epiléptico.","guid":"arinTtSMVN_WDZWc_Wq7XQ","children":[]},{"id":"28","parent":"20","text":"• Debilidad respiratoria neuromuscular.","guid":"nFU6ZUUiDTNtH9oRuK0jYA","children":[]}]},{"id":"29","parent":"1","text":"5. Mielitis infecciosa","guid":"5AZtcOngW2-ee4kbYeaGpw","children":[{"id":"30","parent":"29","text":"• Primariamente viral (VHS, VVZ) → tto con antivirales (aciclovir).","guid":"e7KEEFp-WxdQPBZIyvp6lw","children":[]},{"id":"31","parent":"29","text":"• Parálisis flácida aguda → infección citolítica de células del asta anterior.","guid":"OqO5duKQebQuO3_2x9B2lw","children":[]}]},{"id":"32","parent":"1","text":"6. Diagnóstico y\\Ntratamiento","guid":"uLKL22q_6V41pzmnsK4P4Q","children":[{"id":"33","parent":"32","text":"• Identificación rápida → muestra LCR (punción lumbar).","guid":"5_ou4CGUKPxOhVZPJGbQCA","children":[]},{"id":"34","parent":"32","text":"• Tto empírico inmediato.","guid":"cLbEppTeqKGkwHDfJDAywA","children":[]},{"id":"35","parent":"32","text":"• Corticoides en encefalitis postviral o indistinguible de inflamación.","guid":"Y9rIeyGNNA9_hmTzEHmgyw","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"36","parent":"0","text":"Meningitis y\\NVentriculitis","guid":"NBbgfP7BCZm0sjBHmbzR8w","children":[{"id":"37","parent":"36","text":"1. Definiciones","guid":"","children":[{"id":"38","parent":"37","text":"• Meningitis: inflamación de las meninges.","guid":"T3PATDkI-fsqb29UjKqjoA","children":[]},{"id":"39","parent":"37","text":"• Ventriculitis: inflamación del revestimiento ependimario ventricular.","guid":"Xzayn9cIK800-UMRtqDwaA","children":[]},{"id":"40","parent":"37","text":"• Ambas requieren tto empírico inmediato mientras se espera resultado LCR.","guid":"FrNu_lqc31OyZSabY34a4Q","children":[]}]},{"id":"41","parent":"36","text":"2. Etiología","guid":"","children":[{"id":"42","parent":"41","text":"• Meningitis bacteriana: alta morbimortalidad.","guid":"nGOX7_O7zZkVe8YJEPglpg","children":[]},{"id":"43","parent":"41","text":"• Diferencias en incidencia/mortalidad entre países → ↓ en países de ingresos altos\\N(0.9/100,000 vs. 80/100, 000) y mortalidad (10% vs. 58%).","guid":"5o34KNAiygK_QvDG5xZb9A","children":[]},{"id":"44","parent":"41","text":"• Factores contribuyentes: vacunación, uso de dexametasona, VIH,\\Nregulación de seguridad alimentaria (Listeria).","guid":"Y0c48TD9hsUFdlLsLCDi8A","children":[]},{"id":"45","parent":"41","text":"• En países desarrollados: ↓ exposición neonatal a S. agalactiae\\N(profilaxis antibiótica en embarazo).","guid":"8qML8bELJl-nWIy5HqcBog","children":[]}]},{"id":"46","parent":"36","text":"3. Patógenos comunes según\\Nedad/ambiente","guid":"tM1saeN7hdoU6tBor1WXgg","children":[{"id":"47","parent":"46","text":"• Adquirida fuera\\Ndel hospital:","guid":"Jps9W1Pla8zLYJ8R3sTgNw","children":[{"id":"48","parent":"47","text":"• Adultos >2 años: S. pneumoniae y N. meningitidis →\\Ntto empírico con vancomicina + ceftriaxona/cefotaxima.","guid":"3bJbvx09kP-Fy1i1vymwLg","children":[]},{"id":"49","parent":"47","text":"• Adultos >50 años/inmunosupresos: ↑ riesgo de\\NL. monocytogenes → añadir ampicilina.","guid":"n5rlLS_KJiQBwfTUSw96Dw","children":[]},{"id":"50","parent":"47","text":"• Neonatos: S. agalactiae, E. coli, L. monocytogenes\\N→ ampicilina + cefotaxima/aminoglucósido.","guid":"q_yXZjrLDlW5tOM3bhXotA","children":[]},{"id":"51","parent":"47","text":"• Lactantes 1-23 meses: riesgo de E. coli, S. agalactiae\\N+ patógenos comunes adultos.","guid":"jVAcDmiFbbg9pp_npsvPdw","children":[]}]},{"id":"52","parent":"46","text":"• Meningitis asociada a\\Ncuidados de salud:","guid":"Wn3MKybbID5fs43LjoWhDQ","children":[{"id":"53","parent":"52","text":"• Relacionada con instrumentación S.N.\\N(catéteres, derivaciones, bombas).","guid":"sFXIc59zfUmNUk2BkMuMgQ","children":[]},{"id":"54","parent":"52","text":"• Tto empírico: vancomicina + cobertura anti-Pseudomonas.","guid":"xs-U6nDFuWTSDOLpYnQ2Uw","children":[]}]},{"id":"55","parent":"46","text":"• Retirar dispositivo infectado (derivaciones,\\Ncatéteres ventriculares, estimuladores).","guid":"7q-w_Y3epW4tJGu-rvS1uQ","children":[]}]},{"id":"56","parent":"36","text":"4. Tratamiento\\Nespecífico","guid":"r_UfN1VNzBNplZVCJizZsQ","children":[{"id":"57","parent":"56","text":"• Dexametasona: mejora mortalidad, ↓ complicaciones (excepto L. monocytogenes).","guid":"FytcOXO4rfQaz9hY59cWRg","children":[]},{"id":"58","parent":"56","text":"• Infección por gram(-) resistente: combinación intraventricular + IV\\N→ mejoría en mortalidad y aclaramiento vs. solo IV (n=13).","guid":"qcsYGC1sRkCSmmzSF_GHDw","children":[]}]},{"id":"59","parent":"36","text":"5. Terapia\\Nintratecal","guid":"rWj99hXn9lX9uYcsOVkGqQ","children":[{"id":"60","parent":"59","text":"• Considerar cuando ATB sistémico no penetra la BHE.","guid":"3JXL_ojY3z0Vwo_VDJH2PA","children":[]},{"id":"61","parent":"59","text":"• Riesgo: toxicidad directa, convulsiones.","guid":"gtGhzPQNCvCx-rkriUIWrQ","children":[]},{"id":"62","parent":"59","text":"• Requiere ATB sin conservantes y consulta con infectología y farmacia.","guid":"qyb-sPE4UPEDgHA4W9CE8Q","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"63","parent":"0","text":"Absceso y\\Nempiema del SNC","guid":"giUFI2OHWSjdQemmFYOJbw","children":[{"id":"64","parent":"63","text":"1. Definición","guid":"","children":[{"id":"65","parent":"64","text":"• Absceso: colección purulenta en parénquima cerebral/medular o espacio epidural.","guid":"1DFAZRFthxx8vnj-HAr4kw","children":[]},{"id":"66","parent":"64","text":"• Empiema: colección en espacio subdural.","guid":"KV8dcthd8ZRbgAkmmwjF4Q","children":[]},{"id":"67","parent":"64","text":"• Ambos → necrosis central + cápsula circundante.","guid":"R0dP-aTEN4NtDTpXKGOwmw","children":[]}]},{"id":"68","parent":"63","text":"2. Etiología","guid":"","children":[{"id":"69","parent":"68","text":"•  50% precedidos por infecciones extraneurales\\N(otitis, sinusitis, mastoiditis, infecciones dentales).","guid":"NHTvik8bAQbAzPDm8aBW-w","children":[]},{"id":"70","parent":"68","text":"• Vía de diseminación: directa o hematógena.","guid":"4NwfioUhLLGRc4w_zGPqow","children":[]},{"id":"71","parent":"68","text":"• Absceso espinal: espacio epidural → discitis, osteomielitis.","guid":"bo5RJn_gSBlAv2dwRCFeiw","children":[]},{"id":"72","parent":"68","text":"• Infecciones precedentes: abscesos cutáneos/tejidos\\Nblandos, endocarditis, faringitis, bacteriemia.","guid":"0TW9bPbCOhPeplLNQCaEWg","children":[]}]},{"id":"73","parent":"63","text":"3. Diagnóstico","guid":"2BxNtLd2dWLvUDgRLOwI8Q","children":[{"id":"74","parent":"73","text":"• CT: puede pasar desapercibido\\N(proximidad a hueso, isodensidad).","guid":"UoXqLCTnSNOVFONBmptX2g","children":[]},{"id":"75","parent":"73","text":"• MRI: método diagnóstico de elección.","guid":"8moqxU1vkU8fG_dGZ0H-SQ","children":[]}]},{"id":"76","parent":"63","text":"4. Tratamiento","guid":"G0EwZNdv8wseOIUVRyY5Ow","children":[{"id":"77","parent":"76","text":"• Tto empírico: vancomicina + ceftriaxona + metronidazol.","guid":"sORY_fNBadVQgms-sc3cOg","children":[]},{"id":"78","parent":"76","text":"• Fuente primaria → identificación/control (neurocirugía, otorrinolaringología).","guid":"c2BUZ-vrshtC2BiVowLCpA","children":[]},{"id":"79","parent":"76","text":"• Lavado subdural y sinusal si es necesario.","guid":"_fRUJaRAZGoths4QYWnabw","children":[]},{"id":"80","parent":"76","text":"• Anticonvulsivos si convulsiones (p. ej. lorazepam, levetiracetam, lacosamida).","guid":"WMs94v3fwLwHPhDVBJ2Ecw","children":[]}]},{"id":"81","parent":"63","text":"5. Caso clínico\\N(Caso 8-1)","guid":"vTrb644k3K7WDdsHIHKtgA","children":[{"id":"82","parent":"81","text":"• Mujer 31 años → fiebre, fatiga, drenaje nasal purulento, ceftriaxona + metronidazol,\\Nconvulsiones controladas con lorazepam y levetiracetam.","guid":"Wn9dzlMbJuTgXGfZe8svSA","children":[]},{"id":"83","parent":"81","text":"• Hallazgos: ventriculitis, cerebritis, sinusitis difusa, empiema subdural.","guid":"tAs-4SjjbPaxvsu7BqgsHA","children":[]},{"id":"84","parent":"81","text":"• Aislamiento de S. pneumoniae, tto definitivo con ceftriaxona 14 días.","guid":"_fuCvzeS5JMU0hs6hUTWCw","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"85","parent":"0","text":"Absceso y Empiema del SNC:\\NPatógenos comunes y diseminación","guid":"yZYpqcOiKLe5xgJ5LuNlPQ","children":[{"id":"86","parent":"85","text":"1. Definición","guid":"","children":[{"id":"87","parent":"86","text":"• Absceso: colección purulenta en parénquima cerebral o médula espinal/espacio epidural.","guid":"M7IwazoMKhi6LxIkNUhu9Q","children":[]},{"id":"88","parent":"86","text":"• Empiema: colección purulenta en espacio subdural.","guid":"A20dqinUfnG2r1MEy0GeAA","children":[]}]},{"id":"89","parent":"85","text":"2. Patógenos según\\Ninfección primaria","guid":"bA4Ln0xBK_OANwYecsO7lQ","children":[{"id":"90","parent":"89","text":"• Otitis (diseminación contigua) → Streptococcus, Enterobacter, Pseudomonas, anaerobios.","guid":"cdXTGf5dhpBOeStYuWuuQQ","children":[]},{"id":"91","parent":"89","text":"• Sinusitis (contigua) → Streptococcus, Staphylococcus, Haemophilus, anaerobios.","guid":"nC3AEFpCCQGCUl4asCRmbg","children":[]},{"id":"92","parent":"89","text":"• Infección dental (hematógena) → Streptococcus aeróbico, anaerobios.","guid":"8g8L5wi17mQplLeKfjD2uA","children":[]},{"id":"93","parent":"89","text":"• Absceso cutáneo o muscular (contigua/hematógena) → Staphylococcus, Streptococcus.","guid":"M9Nry8vLenPm_-IYQCkDAg","children":[]},{"id":"94","parent":"89","text":"• Endocarditis (hematógena) → Staphylococcus, Streptococcus, Enterococcus, HACEK.","guid":"m6_1venyt8JPQmObm-BhWQ","children":[]},{"id":"95","parent":"89","text":"• Pulmonar (hematógena) → Staphylococcus, Streptococcus, Enterococcus, Nocardia, anaerobios.","guid":"wuNbIoD7YH96pT0r2PxNgg","children":[]},{"id":"96","parent":"89","text":"• Neurocirugía (directa/contigua) → Staphylococcus, Streptococcus, Enterobacter, Pseudomonas, anaerobios.","guid":"FFwPWARdUqCUsZsjdLA4jA","children":[]},{"id":"97","parent":"89","text":"• Trauma penetrante (directa/contigua/hematógena) → Staphylococcus, Streptococcus, Enterobacter, Pseudomonas, anaerobios.","guid":"sm3WTDzPQjM7E4io1gRvcg","children":[]}]},{"id":"98","parent":"85","text":"3. Inmunocomprometidos","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"99","parent":"85","text":"• Riesgo: Nocardia,\\NActinomyces, Mycobacterium\\Nspp.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"100","parent":"85","text":"• Infecciones fúngicas comunes: Aspergillus,\\NCryptococcus, Candida, Blastomyces,\\NHistoplasma, Coccidioides, Mucorales.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"101","parent":"85","text":"• Considerar Toxoplasma,\\NAcanthamoeba en escenarios\\Nclínicos apropiados.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"102","parent":"85","text":"4. Diagnóstico","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"103","parent":"85","text":"• Fuente primaria → cultivo o\\Nmuestra quirúrgica.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"104","parent":"85","text":"• Avances en espectroscopía por RM →\\Nayuda a diferenciar abscesos bacterianos,\\Nfúngicos o tuberculosos.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"105","parent":"85","text":"5. Tratamiento y manejo","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"106","parent":"85","text":"• Cobertura empírica apropiada →\\Nconsulta con infectología.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"107","parent":"85","text":"• Aspiración/exéresis quirúrgica\\Nindicada en abscesos únicos,\\Nsintomáticos, accesibles o grandes.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"108","parent":"85","text":"• Monitoreo mediante imágenes semanales\\Npara evaluar respuesta al tto.","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"109","parent":"0","text":"Referencias:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"110","parent":"109","text":"1. Reynolds, A. S. (2024).\\NNeuroinfectious emergencies.\\NContinuum (Minneap Minn), 30(3),\\N757-780.","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"111","parent":"0","text":"Complicaciones de\\Ninfecciones neurológicas","guid":"cvOnpNG1uoXCptzBgB7mOw","children":[{"id":"112","parent":"111","text":"1. Edema\\Ncerebral","guid":"HLyRy6m5pyfMwbFbprhxSQ","children":[{"id":"113","parent":"112","text":"• Asociado a meningitis/encefalitis.","guid":"57dT9Q6NgyW0OLI1304gDg","children":[]},{"id":"114","parent":"112","text":"• 15% de los pacientes con encefalitis presentan edema cerebral\\N→ alta mortalidad.","guid":"I_ZrBWgreoE_b-qMzVU7lg","children":[]},{"id":"115","parent":"112","text":"• Contribuye a herniación cerebral y efecto de masa (en abscesos).","guid":"FSlFWWZRDO8OsvDz_5WRNg","children":[]},{"id":"116","parent":"112","text":"• Tto: Dexametasona (excepto en infecciones por L. monocytogenes o Cryptococcus).","guid":"vxP-Krnnz4ZrwFXsEMA7qA","children":[]},{"id":"117","parent":"112","text":"• Monitoreo: presión intracraneal (EVD) o chequeos neurológicos frecuentes.","guid":"YmHKYKu1QV6OZpbQaZBngw","children":[]}]},{"id":"118","parent":"111","text":"2. Hidrocefalia","guid":"","children":[{"id":"119","parent":"118","text":"• Causa síntomas: cefalea, letargo, ↓ perfusión cerebral, muerte.","guid":"s6xcC1l2hqOck3QDPW62ow","children":[]},{"id":"120","parent":"118","text":"• Tipos:","guid":"wIS5uuz-BOeXXg0P093ZJQ","children":[{"id":"121","parent":"120","text":"• Obstructiva: causada por obstrucción de flujo LCR (edema, infección leptomeníngea).","guid":"U0f3pp_SRMv5FrkLvA3k0Q","children":[{"id":"122","parent":"121","text":"- Contraindicado PL → EVD + drenaje limitado si hay riesgo de herniación.","guid":"VpmG6YaAovEAxWAPtFGX3w","children":[]}]},{"id":"123","parent":"120","text":"• Comunicante: causado por detritos (p.ej. cápsulas de Cryptococcus).","guid":"Jr3NBd2csDc4JPzTY3At4w","children":[]}]},{"id":"124","parent":"118","text":"• Hidrocefalia persistente post-infección → derivación\\NLCR (VP shunt, endoscopía).","guid":"o37zsodvkozyR0A9f1MpmQ","children":[]}]},{"id":"125","parent":"111","text":"3. Complicaciones\\Nadicionales","guid":"4QROSujVmI0HvlAJKMdX8w","children":[{"id":"126","parent":"125","text":"• Vasoespasmo: resultado de meningitis (p. ej., meningitis estreptocócica).","guid":"H0kX1PnX7p0Ixvhsm6TDEA","children":[]},{"id":"127","parent":"125","text":"• Trombosis del seno cavernoso:\\Ninfecciones como mucormicosis.","guid":"XaNAZbDB1U7gGqCuLFCwhw","children":[]},{"id":"128","parent":"125","text":"• Hemorragia cerebral: aneurismas\\Nmicóticos por endocarditis infecciosa.","guid":"2wsCj14CiYmVB1YMEXrm4A","children":[]},{"id":"129","parent":"125","text":"• Status epiléptico:\\Nmeningitis severa.","guid":"oIfGNgCtYnlH7IOYm_EpBQ","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"130","parent":"0","text":"- Tto: PL, drenaje\\Nlumbar, EVD.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"131","parent":"0","text":"Referencias:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"132","parent":"131","text":"1. Reynolds, A. S. (2024).\\NNeuroinfectious emergencies.\\NContinuum (Minneap Minn), 30(3),\\N757-780.","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"133","parent":"0","text":"Vasculopatía e\\NIsquemia Cerebral","guid":"9AmOBbYcDK69cKy1YERCrA","children":[{"id":"134","parent":"133","text":"1. Definición","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"135","parent":"133","text":"• Vasculopatía: inflamación/invasión directa\\Nde la pared vascular → infecciones (p.ej.\\Naspergilosis, mucormicosis).","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"136","parent":"133","text":"• Causa más común: inflamación\\Nadyacente con proliferación intimal.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"137","parent":"133","text":"2. Infecciones asociadas\\Na ACV isquémico","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"138","parent":"133","text":"• Meningitis neumocócica →\\NInfartos en 36% de los casos.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"139","parent":"133","text":"• Otras infecciones:\\Ntuberculosis, VHS, varicela\\Nzóster.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"140","parent":"133","text":"3. Caso clínico\\N(Caso 8-3)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"141","parent":"133","text":"• Paciente 58 años, emigrante\\Nde Sudamérica, con confusión\\Ne incontinencia.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"142","parent":"133","text":"• Fiebre, hipoxemia\\N→ intubación.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"143","parent":"133","text":"• RM → meningitis basal con\\Nedema vasogénico severo.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"144","parent":"133","text":"• PL: glucosa 13 mg/dL, proteínas 165\\Nmg/dL, leucocitos 360/mm3.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"145","parent":"133","text":"• Empírico: rifampicina, isoniazida,\\Npirazinamida, etambutol, dexametasona,\\Nvancomicina, ceftriaxona, ampicilina.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"146","parent":"133","text":"• Vasculopatía en MRA →\\Ntratamiento con verapamilo\\Nintraarterial y milrinona sistémica.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"147","parent":"133","text":"• Desarrollo de ACV isquémico\\Nextenso → diagnóstico post mortem\\Nde tuberculosis cerebral.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"148","parent":"133","text":"4. Tratamiento","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"149","parent":"133","text":"• Antituberculosos empíricos en\\Nsospecha alta, incluso sin\\Nconfirmación diagnóstica.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"150","parent":"133","text":"• Manejo de complicaciones: hipertensión\\Nintracraneal, ACV, vasculopatía.","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"151","parent":"0","text":"Referencias:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"152","parent":"151","text":"1. Reynolds, A. S. (2024).\\NNeuroinfectious emergencies.\\NContinuum (Minneap Minn), 30(3),\\N757-780.","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"153","parent":"0","text":"Vasculopatía e infarto isquémico en\\Ninfecciones neurológicas","guid":"Ap5wdBWm0RnHj5tf6TjJPw","children":[{"id":"154","parent":"153","text":"1. Vasculopatía","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"155","parent":"153","text":"• Causada por invasión directa\\Nde la pared vascular o\\Ninflamación adyacente.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"156","parent":"153","text":"• Infecciones angioinvasivas\\Nclásicas: Aspergillus, Mucorales.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"157","parent":"153","text":"• Asociadas a vasculopatía → ACV\\Nisquémico o hemorrágico.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"158","parent":"153","text":"2. Infecciones asociadas\\Na ACV isquémico","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"159","parent":"153","text":"• Meningitis neumocócica →\\Ninfartos en 36% de los casos.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"160","parent":"153","text":"• Meningitis meningocócica →\\N9% de los pacientes.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"161","parent":"153","text":"• Meningitis tuberculosa →\\N17% de los pacientes.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"162","parent":"153","text":"• Cryptococcus → 26% con infartos\\Nlacunares en ganglios basales.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"163","parent":"153","text":"• VHS, VZV, HIV → vasculopatía y\\NACV detectados por imágenes de\\Nla pared vascular.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"164","parent":"153","text":"• Borrelia burgdorferi (Lyme) →\\NACV isquémico/hemorrágico en\\N1% de los infectados.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"165","parent":"153","text":"3. Diagnóstico y\\Ntratamiento","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"166","parent":"153","text":"• Imágenes: Angiografía por\\Nsustracción digital (DSA) →\\Ndiagnóstico definitivo.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"167","parent":"153","text":"• Tratamiento empírico:\\NAntimicrobianos dirigidos\\Nsegún sospecha etiológica.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"168","parent":"153","text":"• Anticoagulación en trombosis\\Nvenosa séptica es controvertida →\\Nriesgo de hemorragia.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"169","parent":"153","text":"4. Caso clínico\\N(Caso 8-3)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"170","parent":"153","text":"• Paciente 58 años, meningitis basal,\\Nhipertensión intracraneal, ACV isquémico,\\Ndiagnóstico de tuberculosis post mortem.","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"171","parent":"0","text":"Referencias:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"172","parent":"171","text":"1. Reynolds, A. S. (2024).\\NNeuroinfectious emergencies.\\NContinuum (Minneap Minn), 30(3),\\N757-780.","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"173","parent":"0","text":"Compresión medular","guid":"PicXn-hnI4mepnrW0bccYw","children":[{"id":"174","parent":"173","text":"1. Definición","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"175","parent":"173","text":"• El absceso epidural espinal puede comprimir la médula\\Nespinal por compresión directa, edema (obstrucción del\\Ndrenaje venoso) o isquemia local.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"176","parent":"173","text":"2. Diagnóstico","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"177","parent":"173","text":"• Difícil de detectar temprano por\\Nsíntomas inespecíficos.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"178","parent":"173","text":"• Se recomienda imagen de toda la columna\\Ncuando se identifica un absceso epidural, debido\\Na la diseminación hematógena.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"179","parent":"173","text":"3. Tratamiento médico","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"180","parent":"173","text":"• Antimicrobianos de amplio\\Nespectro de 4 a 12 semanas.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"181","parent":"173","text":"• La terapia médica sola falla en 40% de los casos,\\Nparticularmente en pacientes mayores,\\Ninmunocomprometidos o con infecciones por S.\\Naureus resistente a meticilina (MRSA).","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"182","parent":"173","text":"4. Tratamiento quirúrgico","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"183","parent":"173","text":"• Deterioro neurológico → cirugía necesaria\\N(laminectomía descompresiva).","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"184","parent":"173","text":"• Abscesos anteriores pueden\\Nrequerir corpectomía.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"185","parent":"173","text":"• Aspiración con aguja guiada por imagen para\\Npacientes de alto riesgo quirúrgico o con\\Nabscesos únicos accesibles.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"186","parent":"173","text":"5. Esteroides","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"187","parent":"173","text":"• Uso a corto plazo para\\Nreducir el efecto de masa.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"188","parent":"173","text":"• Prolongación del uso ↓\\Npenetración de antimicrobianos.","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"189","parent":"0","text":"Referencias:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"190","parent":"189","text":"1. Reynolds, A. S. (2024).\\NNeuroinfectious emergencies.\\NContinuum (Minneap Minn), 30(3),\\N757-780.","guid":"","children":[]}]}]},"node_count":190,"relations":[],"cross_references":[],"specialty":"Infectología","folder":"Entidades clínicas/Infectología","filename":"Infecciones del SNC-2024-1","id":"map_1146","resolved_references":[],"title_raw":"Infecciones del SNC-2024-1"}